## Description {#details}

Find all cycles in a control-flow graph, including irreducible loops.

See docs/CycleTerminology.rst for a formal definition of cycles.

Briefly:
<ul>
<li>A cycle is a generalization of a loop which can represent irreducible control flow.</li>
<li>Cycles identified in a program are implementation defined, depending on the DFS traversal chosen.</li>
<li>Cycles are well-nested, and form a forest with a parent-child relationship.</li>
<li>In any choice of DFS, every natural loop L is represented by a unique cycle C which is a superset of L.</li>
<li>In the absence of irreducible control flow, the cycles are exactly the natural loops in the program.</li>
</ul>
